const formRef = useRef(); const handleInputChange = (e) => { const { name, value } = e.target; setFormData(prevState => ({ ...prevState, [name]: value })); }; const handlePrint = useReactToPrint({ content: () => formRef.current, documentTitle: 'History and Physical Examination', onBeforeGetContent: () => { return new Promise((resolve) => { resolve(); }); }, onAfterPrint: () => { console.log('Print completed'); }, }); // Fallback print function using browser's native print const handlePrintFallback = () => { const printContent = formRef.current; if (printContent) { const printWindow = window.open('', '_blank'); printWindow.document.write(` History and Physical Examination ${printContent.innerHTML} `); printWindow.document.close(); printWindow.focus(); printWindow.print(); printWindow.close(); } }; const handlePrintClick = () => { try { handlePrint();
